threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Mirai botnet variant targeting ARM-based Linux devices. It exhibits characteristic botnet behaviors, including: 1) Telnet brute-forcing using an extensive embedded list of default credentials (e.g., 'root:xirtam', 'admin:admin', 'support:1234') found in function sub_135fc. 2) Competitive process management by enumerating the /proc filesystem, network connections (/proc/net/tcp), and process maps to identify and terminate rival botnet processes. 3) Automated propagation via multi-protocol download commands (HTTP, TFTP, FTP) executed through Busybox to fetch and run secondary shell scripts such as 'wget.sh', 'tftp.sh', and 'curl.sh'. 4) Evasion techniques including daemonization via /dev/null and /dev/console redirection.
